---
name: Google Search Function Test
description: Minimal prompt to exercise internal google_search function tool with capture/report
version: 1.0.0

inputs:
  record:
    description: Optional source record
    type: object
    default: {}

model:
  api: responses
  configuration:
    connection: openai_conn
    model: gpt-5-mini
    type: openai_chat
    tools:
      - type: function
        function:
          name: google_search
          description: Execute Google search via MCP tool for testing
          parameters:
            type: object
            properties:
              query:
                type: string
                description: Search query
              num_results:
                type: integer
                description: Number of results
                default: 5
              language:
                type: string
                description: Language code
                default: "en"
              country:
                type: string
                description: Country/region code
                default: "za"
            required: ["query"]

processing_config:
  source_collection: Domain
  mode_description: Test prompt to validate google_search function tool path

---

system:
You are a tool-calling test assistant.

Your task is to call the function tool google_search with an appropriate query:

Query to use: "Yoco company overview payments South Africa"
num_results: 5
language: "en"
country: "za"

After the tool call returns, summarize the top 3 result titles and URLs in one short paragraph.

Output policy:
- If no results are returned, state "unknown" for titles/URLs rather than leaving fields empty.

user:
Run the google_search function tool as instructed and then provide a brief confirmation.
